                            <comment id="16303393" author="erickerickson" created="Mon, 25 Dec 2017 21:28:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Kevin!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For day to day work, especially on a mac where the file limit is 10K (or I haven&apos;t bothered to figure out the magic), the check quickly becomes nagware. So you can set &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SOLR_ULIMIT_CHECKS=false&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; in your profile. Also works in solr.in.sh if you&apos;d prefer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
